   <abstract displayLabel="Description">Garrison tells his wife that he drew 5 months pay and will send her "20 Dollars by Express."</abstract>
   <note type="biographical/historical" displayLabel="Biographical Note">Abraham Garrison was a private in the 161st New York Infantry Regiment, which was organized in October 1862. He spent the duration of his service in Louisiana and died of typhoid fever and dysentery on September 17, 1863.</note>
